  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Let children hear the mighty deeds Which God performed of old; Which in our younger years we saw, And which our fathers told.",
    "v2": "He bids us make His glories known, His works of pow&#39;r and grace; And we&#39;ll convey His wonders down Through every rising race.",
    "v3": "Our lips shall tell them to our sons, And they again to theirs; That genera- tions yet unborn May teach them to their heirs.",
    "v4": "Thus shall they learn in God alone Their hope securely stands, That they may ne&#39;er forget His work But practice His commands."
  },
